htmlElements.name: Hyperlink
htmlElements.description: Defines a hyperlink to webpages, files, email address, telephone numbers, SMS numbers, data URLs, or other URLs.

htmlElements.name: Abbreviation
htmlElements.description: Defines an abbreviation or an acronym, like HTML, CSS, or HTTP.

htmlElements.name: Address
htmlElements.description: Defines the contact information for the author/owner of a document or an article.

htmlElements.name: Image Map Area
htmlElements.description: Defines an area inside an image map.

htmlElements.name: Article
htmlElements.description: Defines a self-contained composition in a document, page, application, or site.

htmlElements.name: Aside
htmlElements.description: Defines a portion of a document whose content is only indirectly related to the document's main content.

htmlElements.name: Audio
htmlElements.description: Embeds sound content in documents.

htmlElements.name: Bold
htmlElements.description: Defines bold text to draw the reader's attention to the element's contents

htmlElements.name: Base
htmlElements.description: Specifies the base URL for all relative URLs in the document.

htmlElements.name: Bidirectional Isolation
htmlElements.description: Isolates a part of text that might be formatted in a different direction from other text outside it.

htmlElements.name: Bidirectional Text Override
htmlElements.description: Overrides the current directionality of text, so that the text within is rendered in a different direction.

htmlElements.name: Blockquote
htmlElements.description: Defines a section that is quoted from another source.

htmlElements.name: Body
htmlElements.description: Defines the document's body, or content.

htmlElements.name: Break
htmlElements.description: Produces a line break in text (carriage-return).

htmlElements.name: Button
htmlElements.description: Defines a clickable button.

htmlElements.name: Canvas
htmlElements.description: Used to draw graphics, on the fly, via scripting (usually JavaScript).

htmlElements.name: Caption
htmlElements.description: Defines the caption (or title) of a table.

htmlElements.name: Cite
htmlElements.description: Defines the title of a cited creative work (e.g. a book, a song, a movie, a TV show, a painting, a sculpture, etc.).

htmlElements.name: Code
htmlElements.description: Defines a short fragment of computer code.

htmlElements.name: Column
htmlElements.description: Defines a column within a table and is used for defining common semantics on all common cells.

htmlElements.name: Column Group
htmlElements.description: Defines a group of columns within a table.

htmlElements.name: Data
htmlElements.description: Adds a machine-readable translation of data into a more human-readable form.

htmlElements.name: Data List
htmlElements.description: Contains a set of <option> elements that represent the permissible or recommended options available to users.

htmlElements.name: Description Details
htmlElements.description: Provides the description, definition, or value for the preceding term in a description list.

htmlElements.name: Deleted Text
htmlElements.description: Defines text that has been deleted from a document.

htmlElements.name: Details
htmlElements.description: Defines additional details that the user can view or hide.

htmlElements.name: Definition
htmlElements.description: Indicates the term being defined within the context of a definition phrase or sentence.

htmlElements.name: Dialog
htmlElements.description: Represents a modal or non-modal dialog box or other interactive component, such as a dismissible alert, inspector, or subwindow.

htmlElements.name: Container
htmlElements.description: Defines a generic container for flow content, which does not inherently represent anything.

htmlElements.name: Description List
htmlElements.description: Defines a description list.

htmlElements.name: Description Term
htmlElements.description: Defines a term (or name) in a description list.

htmlElements.name: Emphasis
htmlElements.description: Defines emphasized text.

htmlElements.name: Embed
htmlElements.description: Embeds external content at the specified point in the document.

htmlElements.name: Field Set
htmlElements.description: Groups related elements in a form.

htmlElements.name: Figure Caption
htmlElements.description: Defines a caption or legend for a <figure> element.

htmlElements.name: Figure
htmlElements.description: Represents self-contained content, potentially with an optional caption, which is specified using the <figcaption> element.

htmlElements.name: Footer
htmlElements.description: Defines a footer for a document or section.

htmlElements.name: Form
htmlElements.description: Represents a document section containing interactive controls for submitting information.

htmlElements.name: Heading
htmlElements.description: Defines the highest-level heading for a section or subsection.

htmlElements.name: Heading
htmlElements.description: Defines the second-level heading for a section or subsection.

htmlElements.name: Heading
htmlElements.description: Defines the third-level heading for a section or subsection.

htmlElements.name: Heading
htmlElements.description: Defines the fourth-level heading for a section or subsection.

htmlElements.name: Heading
htmlElements.description: Defines the fifth-level heading for a section or subsection.

htmlElements.name: Heading
htmlElements.description: Defines the sixth-level heading for a section or subsection.

htmlElements.name: Head
htmlElements.description: Contains machine-readable information (metadata) about the document, like its title, scripts, and style sheets.

htmlElements.name: Header
htmlElements.description: Represents introductory content, typically a group of introductory or navigational aids.

htmlElements.name: Heading Group
htmlElements.description: Represents a heading and groups it with the content it's related to.

htmlElements.name: Horizontal Rule
htmlElements.description: Represents a thematic break between paragraph-level elements.

htmlElements.name: HTML
htmlElements.description: Represents the root (top-level element) of an HTML document, so it is also referred to as the root element.

htmlElements.name: Idiomatic Text
htmlElements.description: Represents a range of text that is set off from the normal text for some reason, like idiomatic text, technical terms, taxonomical designations, among others.

htmlElements.name: Iframe
htmlElements.description: Represents a nested browsing context, effectively embedding another HTML page into the current page.

htmlElements.name: Image
htmlElements.description: Embeds an image into the document.

htmlElements.name: Input
htmlElements.description: Represents an interactive control for web-based forms in order to accept data from the user.

htmlElements.name: Inserted Text
htmlElements.description: Represents a range of text that has been added to a document.

htmlElements.name: Keyboard Input
htmlElements.description: Represents user input, typically keyboard input.

htmlElements.name: Label
htmlElements.description: Represents a caption for an item in a user interface.

htmlElements.name: Legend
htmlElements.description: Represents a caption for the content of its parent fieldset.

htmlElements.name: List Item
htmlElements.description: Represents a list item.

htmlElements.name: Link
htmlElements.description: Specifies relationships between the current document and an external resource.

htmlElements.name: Main
htmlElements.description: Represents the dominant content of the body of a document.

htmlElements.name: Image Map
htmlElements.description: The map element is used with area elements to define an image map.

htmlElements.name: Mark Text
htmlElements.description: Represents text which is marked or highlighted for reference purposes.

htmlElements.name: Menu
htmlElements.description: Represents a semantic alternative to a list of items, for example, a list of commands.

htmlElements.name: Meta
htmlElements.description: Represents metadata that cannot be represented by other HTML meta-related elements.

htmlElements.name: Meter
htmlElements.description: Represents a scalar measurement within a known range, or a fractional value.

htmlElements.name: Navigation
htmlElements.description: Represents a section of a page that links to other pages or to parts within the page.

htmlElements.name: No Script
htmlElements.description: The noscript element defines a section of HTML to be inserted if a script type on the page is unsupported or if scripting is currently turned off in the browser.

htmlElements.name: Object
htmlElements.description: Represents an external resource, which can be treated as an image, a nested browsing context, or a resource to be handled by a plugin.

htmlElements.name: Ordered List
htmlElements.description: Represents an ordered list of items, typically rendered as a numbered list.

htmlElements.name: Option Group
htmlElements.description: Represents a group of options within a select element.

htmlElements.name: Option
htmlElements.description: Represents an option in a select element or as part of a list of suggestions in a datalist element.

htmlElements.name: Output
htmlElements.description: Represents a container for the result of a calculation or user action.

htmlElements.name: Paragraph
htmlElements.description: Represents a paragraph.

htmlElements.name: Picture
htmlElements.description: The picture element contains zero or more source elements and one img element to provide versions of an image for different display/device scenarios.

htmlElements.name: Preformatted Text
htmlElements.description: Represents preformatted text which is to be presented exactly as written in the HTML file.

htmlElements.name: Progress
htmlElements.description: Represents the completion progress of a task.

htmlElements.name: Quote
htmlElements.description: Represents a short inline quotation.

htmlElements.name: Ruby Parenthesis
htmlElements.description: Represents parentheses around a ruby annotation, used to display the parentheses in browsers that do not support ruby annotations.

htmlElements.name: Ruby Text
htmlElements.description: Represents the text of a ruby annotation, which is used to provide pronunciation, translation, or transliteration information for East Asian typography.

htmlElements.name: Ruby
htmlElements.description: Represents a ruby annotation, which is a small text attached to the main text to indicate pronunciation or meaning.

htmlElements.name: Strikethrough
htmlElements.description: Represents text that is no longer accurate or relevant.

htmlElements.name: Sample Output
htmlElements.description: Represents sample output from a computer program.

htmlElements.name: Script
htmlElements.description: The script element allows authors to include dynamic script and data blocks in their documents.

htmlElements.name: Search
htmlElements.description: Represents a control for searching through a document.

htmlElements.name: Section
htmlElements.description: Represents a generic standalone section of a document.

htmlElements.name: Select
htmlElements.description: Represents a control that provides a menu of options.

htmlElements.name: Slot
htmlElements.description: The slot element is a placeholder inside a web component that you can fill with your own markup.

htmlElements.name: Small
htmlElements.description: Represents side-comments and small print, like copyright and legal text, independent of its styled presentation.

htmlElements.name: Source
htmlElements.description: Specifies one or more media resources for the picture, audio, or video elements.

htmlElements.name: Span
htmlElements.description: The span element is a generic inline container for phrasing content.

htmlElements.name: Strong
htmlElements.description: Represents strong importance, seriousness, or urgency for its contents.

htmlElements.name: Style
htmlElements.description: The style element contains style information for a document, or part of a document.

htmlElements.name: Subscript
htmlElements.description: Represents a subscript.

htmlElements.name: Summary
htmlElements.description: Represents a summary, caption, or legend for the rest of the contents of the summary element's parent details element.

htmlElements.name: Superscript
htmlElements.description: Represents a superscript.

htmlElements.name: Table
htmlElements.description: Represents data in a two-dimensional table.

htmlElements.name: Table Body
htmlElements.description: The tbody element encapsulates a set of table rows (tr elements), indicating that they comprise the body of the table (table).

htmlElements.name: Table Data Cell
htmlElements.description: Represents a data cell in a table.

htmlElements.name: Template
htmlElements.description: The template element is a mechanism for holding client-side content that you don't want to be rendered when the page loads.

htmlElements.name: Text Area
htmlElements.description: Represents a multi-line plain-text editing control.

htmlElements.name: Table Foot
htmlElements.description: The tfoot element encapsulates a set of table rows (tr elements), indicating that they comprise the foot of the table (table).

htmlElements.name: Table Header Cell
htmlElements.description: Represents a header cell in a table.

htmlElements.name: Table Head
htmlElements.description: The thead element encapsulates a set of table rows (tr elements), indicating that they comprise the head of the table (table).

htmlElements.name: Time
htmlElements.description: Represents a specific period in time.

htmlElements.name: Title
htmlElements.description: The title element defines the document's title that is shown in a browser's title bar or a page's tab.

htmlElements.name: Table Row
htmlElements.description: The tr element defines a row of cells in a table.

htmlElements.name: Track
htmlElements.description: The track element is used as a child of the media elements audio and video. It lets you specify timed text tracks (or time-based data), for example to automatically handle subtitles.

htmlElements.name: Unarticulated Annotation
htmlElements.description: Represents a span of inline text which should be rendered in a way that indicates that it has a non-textual annotation.

htmlElements.name: Unordered List
htmlElements.description: Represents an unordered list of items, typically rendered as a bulleted list.

htmlElements.name: Variable
htmlElements.description: Represents a variable in a mathematical expression or a programming context.

htmlElements.name: Video
htmlElements.description: The video element is used to embed video content.

htmlElements.name: Word Break Opportunity
htmlElements.description: Represents a word break opportunity—a position within text where the browser may optionally break a line.

htmlAttributes.name: class

htmlAttributes.name: cols

htmlAttributes.name: colspan

htmlAttributes.description: If the button/input is a submit button (e.g. type="submit"), this attribute sets the submission method to use during form submission (GET, POST, etc.). If this attribute is specified, it overrides the method attribute of the button's form owner.

htmlAttributes.name: formtarget
htmlAttributes.description: If the button/input is a submit button (e.g. type="submit"), this attribute specifies the browsing context (for example, tab, window, or inline frame) in which to display the response that is received after submitting the form. If this attribute is specified, it overrides the target attribute of the button's form owner.
